{"title":"In the Drops: Maap Alt_Road socks, Limar helmet, See.Sense Icon3 lights, Avène cream and the sea","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/maap-alt-road-socks","date":1689329449000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/maap-alt-road-socks\">In the Drops: Maap Alt_Road socks, Limar helmet, See.Sense Icon3 lights, Avène cream and the sea</a></p>\n\n<p>It’s Friday, which is excellent news, but in <em>even</em> better news, the latest edition of <em>Cyclist</em> magazine is out now. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This month’s cover is elite and so is the content inside, which includes Mont Ventoux, Lizzie Deignan’s return, Switzerland’s Susten Pass, Pogačar’s new Tour bike plus much, much more. <a href=\"https://cyclistmag.co.uk/subscriptions\" target=\"_blank\">Subscribe to <em>Cyclist</em></a> or <a href=\"https://shop.cyclist.co.uk/collections/coffee/products/issue-142\" target=\"_blank\">buy issue 142 at the Cyclist Shop</a> to get your copy. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This week it has been a Tour de France frenzy as the race continues to throw out all the stops. From Cav’s sad ending, to the ongoing yellow jersey battle and Philipsen’s impressive display of fast twitch fibres,<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-route-live-tv-guide-startlist-stage-by-stage\" target=\"_blank\"> the 2023 edition</a> is proving to be a brilliant race. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>We have the details of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/team-dsm-firmenich-bike-scott-foil-romain-bardet-tour-de-france\" target=\"_blank\">Romain Bardet’s Scott Foil RC</a>, a <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tour-de-france-2023-week-1\" target=\"_blank\">week one recap</a>, insight into being <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-mechanics\" target=\"_blank\">on the road with the Tour de France mechanics </a>and a beautiful gallery of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/factor-bike-tour-de-france-israel-premier-tech\" target=\"_blank\">Israel-Premier Tech’s Factor Ostro VAM</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Speaking of which, we have all the latest on the new <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/factor-o2-vam-2023\" target=\"_blank\">Factor O2 VAM</a>, a review of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/sram-apex-axs-groupset-review\" target=\"_blank\">SRAM Apex AXS XPLR groupset</a> and the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/quoc-gran-tourer-ii-review\" target=\"_blank\">Quoc Gran Tourer II gravel shoes</a>. There’s also a profile on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/pippa-york\" target=\"_blank\">Pippa York</a> if you fancy a longer read. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>For this week’s <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/in-the-drops\" target=\"_blank\">In the Drops</a>, I’ve picked a few pieces of kit I used on my ride from <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/london-to-tunisia-cycling-route\" target=\"_blank\">London to Tunisia</a>, where I rode for at least eight hours a day for 18 days with temperatures often hitting 34 degrees. So it’s safe to say this kit has been put through the ringer. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get into it.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions\"><img width=\"842\" height=\"297\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/clickable-subs-promo3.jpg\" alt=\"Subscribe to Cyclist Magazine\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/clickable-subs-promo3.jpg 842w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/clickable-subs-promo3-300x106.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/clickable-subs-promo3-768x271.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/clickable-subs-promo3-750x265.jpg 750w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<h2>Maap Alt_Road merino socks</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-2-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-2-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-2-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-2-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-2-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-2-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-2.jpg 972w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Not one to often be bamboozled by socks, the Maap Alt_Road socks have blown my mind. They are frankly the best pair of cycling socks I own. I know you’re thinking, wowzahs that’s a big claim. So what makes them so great?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Made from a merino wool blend, the Alt_Road socks offer typical woollen attributes such as thermoregulation, anti-odour and anti-microbial properties, and also feature arch support and a lightly padded toe area.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It all sounds pretty unextraordinary, right?</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"828\" height=\"552\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-6.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-6.jpg 828w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-6-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-6-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-6-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-6-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Once you look at the socks’ performance, it’s a whole other world of happy feet (penguins not included). </p>\n\n\n\n<p>I wore these socks every day on rotation, 18 days straight and only rinsed them in water every so often to ‘clean’ them. I have had many questions about the state of my feet following my ride but the answer is they were in great shape for all of it. Not a single blister, sore or anything slightly dodgy. My feet felt great both during and after.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And I credit these brilliant socks for the happiness of my lower extremities.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Buy the Maap Alt_Road socks now from <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fmaap.cc%2Fuk%2Fproducts%2Falt_road-trail-sock-black-cypress-green\" target=\"_blank\">Maap (£28)</a></strong></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Limar Air Stratos Mips helmet</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-4.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Pitched as the perfect helmet for bikepacking expeditions, rough roads and everything in between, the Limar Air Stratos helmet is a lightweight, well-ventilated helmet with Mips protection.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is tailored towards everyday practicality rather than aerodynamic performance, featuring a double-layered in-mould shell, which Limar says makes it strong while still being lightweight, at a claimed 240g for a size medium. It also has 15 vents and inner airflow channels for breathability.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-13-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"cyclist on bike selfie\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-13-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-13-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-13-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-13-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-13-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-13-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-13-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-13.jpg 1024w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It is a very good helmet. It copes well with all-day riding in the heat, and I’ve been really impressed with how cool it keeps my head and how quickly the internal pads dry.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And crucially the straps never chafed no matter how sweaty I got.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Buy the Limar Air Stratos Mips helmet now from <a href=\"https://amzn.to/3JUMCdk\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon (£123.24)</a></strong></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>See.Sense Icon3 front and rear light set</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"see.sense lights\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-1.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Lights, camera, Icon3 so the saying doesn’t go, but maybe it should because the See.Sense Icon3 front and rear lights are a cracking illumination combination.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With its 575 lumen front and 350 lumen rear light, the Icon3 range offers powerful brightness, as well as 270° of side visibility and water resistance. I can’t comment on the water resistance because it didn’t rain on my trip (ha) but I can confirm the lights are very bright.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-3-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"see.sense lights back\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-3-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-3-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-3-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-3-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-3-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-3-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-3-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-3.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I used the rear light on any main road I rode on and every day in Italy. It helped me feel seen and safe, keeping any terrifying Italian lorry drivers at bay. The battery for both lights is excellent, lasting for at least 15 hours depending on the mode.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I really liked having the choice of many modes and the ‘Get Me Home Mode’ that automatically dims to save power was very useful.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Buy the See.Sense Icon3 front and rear light set from <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fseesense.cc%2Fproducts%2Fnew-see-sense-icon3%3Fvariant%3D39848828665935\" target=\"_blank\">See.Sense (£179.99)</a></strong></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Avène Cicalfate+ Restorative Protective Cream</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"879\" height=\"586\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-8.jpg\" alt=\"Avene cream\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-8.jpg 879w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-8-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-8-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-8-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-8-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-8-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/ITD-july-emma-8-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>No one wants a saddle sore, but no one is immune to them (I think, at least). Thus, what to do when the dreaded cycling saga strikes? Especially when you are only three days into a rather long ride.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Helpfully, a nice pharmacist somewhere in the Vosges region of France had the answer to my woes, this Avène protective cream. It solved my sores in seconds (OK, not seconds but you get my drift).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The cream forms a protective film where reactivity occurs in the superficial layers of the epidermis and creates a ‘bandage’ effect that protects the skin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Absolutely ideal for any sort of cycling saddle-related agony.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Buy the Avène Cicalfate+ Restorative Protective Cream now from <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.superdrug.com%2Fskin%2Fface-skin-care%2Fexpert-skin%2Fexpert-body-skin-care%2Favene-cicalfate-restorative-cream-sensitive-skin-40ml%2Fp%2F802615\" target=\"_blank\">Superdrug (£9.49)</a></strong></li></ul>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bikepacking-tips\">Tunisia Diaries: 7 things I wish I had known before I set off on my bikepacking adventure</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes\">Tour de France Femmes 2023: Full 956km route announced</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-route-live-tv-guide-startlist-stage-by-stage\">Men’s Tour de France 2023: Stage-by-stage preview and everything you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>What we’re into this week: The sea</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-2-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"seascape with bike\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-2-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-2-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-2-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-2-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-2-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-2.jpg 1024w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>What’s the best way to recover from a long ride? To be honest I’m not entirely sure but I do know that swimming in the sea is a great place to start. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Since my arrival in Tunisia I’ve been mesmerised by the glorious turquoise water. From swimming to stand up paddleboarding, frisbee and beach tennis <em>in </em>the sea, as well as a weekend boat trip, I can’t get enough. The sea makes me so happy. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>I’ve also been doing some yoga but that’s not water-themed.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-1-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"sea\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-1-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-1-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-1-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-1-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-1-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-what-ITD-1.jpg 1024w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, temperatures have been hitting 40+ degrees here. Yes, it is absolutely roasting and no, I haven’t tried to cook an egg outside just yet. But the ocean is the ideal solution for cooling down and for a post-work shake off. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>What’s more, even just watching the waves gently roll into the shore is enough to calm the mind and do some reflecting. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply marvellous. </p>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<p><em><strong>Ad feature</strong></em></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>You’ve watched the Tour de France…….now ride it in 2024!</h3>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-970x648.jpeg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-970x648.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-300x201.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-768x513.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-1536x1027.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-2048x1369.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-750x501.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-1140x762.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/Cyclist-Ad-Pods-Leukemia-July-2023-350x233.jpeg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>Have you got what it takes to ride one of the world’s most gruelling and iconic cycling challenges?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Tour 21 – in partnership with Flutter</strong> and <strong>The Route</strong> see teams of amateur cyclists take on the world’s most gruelling cycling challenges by riding the full Tour de France and Tour de France Femmes avec Zwift routes, one week ahead of the professionals in June and July 2024 to raise funds for national blood cancer, Cure Leukaemia.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Included in the price: accommodation in the official Tour de France hotels, official training and event kit from Official Tour de France kit supplier Santini, all meals and nutritional provision, rolling road closures, dedicated team physios and mechanics and MUCH MORE.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"184\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-970x184.jpg\" alt=\"Tour21 and The Route details\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-970x184.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-300x57.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-768x146.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-1536x292.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-750x143.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21-1140x217.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/1999/02/tour21.jpg 1788w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<div>\n<div><a href=\"https://www.thetour21.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Register your interest in riding the Tour de France</strong></a></div>\n\n\n\n<div><a href=\"https://theroute.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Register your interest in riding the Tour de France Femmes</strong></a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>Ad feature ends</strong></em></p>\n</div></div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/maap-alt-road-socks\">In the Drops: Maap Alt_Road socks, Limar helmet, See.Sense Icon3 lights, Avène cream and the sea</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Emma Cole &#124; Features Writer","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"ec7da91c75db77ab76f2e8aed5a780b122356fd9e4c98a25af5d3903fb32795c","category":"Cycling"}